Maintainer: Nima Hejazi <nh@nimahejazi.org>
Description: Targeted maximum likelihood estimation (TMLE) of population-level
    causal effects under stochastic treatment regimes and related nonparametric
    variable importance analyses. Utilities are provided for computing the TML
    estimate of a counterfactual mean under a stochastically modified
    (continuous-valued) treatment node, under intervention policies that shift
    the natural value of the treatment. The methodology implemented was first
    described by I. Díaz and M.J. van der Laan (2013;
    doi: <10.1111/j.1541-0420.2011.01685.x>) and expanded upon in I. Díaz and
    M.J. van der Laan (2018).
